{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17506807","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17506807"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:47:16+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:47:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2573"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2573","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2573"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.51,0.2,0.02,0.25]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2573"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"34718"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2573","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2573"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2573"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"19663"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4395"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4980"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12800"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2695"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5687"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13047"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42525"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"34718","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/34718"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 30-year-old woman presents with a pruritic, erythematous eruption across her abdomen. She is 30 weeks pregnant with twins. This is her first pregnancy. She denies any previous medical history, including skin disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination there is a polymorphous erythematous papulosquamous eruption across her abdomen, involving striae gravidarum with sparing of the periumbilical area. No other areas of the body are affected.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis clinical picture is consistent with polymorphic eruption of pregnancy, also known as pruritic urticarial papules and plaques of pregnancy (PUPPP). Histology was nonspecific and direct immunofluorescence studies were negative, which is consistent with the diagnosis of PUPPP.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which statement regarding polymorphic eruption of pregnancy is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["It is a malignant dermatosis","It is associated with multiple gestation pregnancies","It is associated with autoimmune disease","It is more common with a female foetus","It commonly lasts until 6 months postpartum"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPolymorphic eruption of pregnancy, otherwise known as pruritic urticarial papules and plaques of pregnancy (PUPPP) commonly occurs in the 3rd trimester and more frequently arises in primigravidae and \u003Cstrong\u003Emultiple pregnancies\u003C/strong\u003E. Pruritic erythematous papules and plaques appear in striae gravidarum, sparing the periumbilical region. The rash can then spread to trunk and proximal limbs. Histology is nonspecific and direct immunofluorescence is negative. Remission occurs within a few days of delivery; the maternal and foetal prognosis is excellent. Emollients, medium potency topical steroids and oral antihistamines can provide relief of symptoms. In severe cases, systemic steroids may be necessary, however this should be prescribed with the input of the obstetric medical team.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Polymorphic eruption of pregnancy, otherwise known as pruritic urticarial papules and plaques of pregnancy (PUPPP) is a common pruritic dermatosis of pregnancy that commonly occurs in the 3rd trimester and resolves on delivery."],"references":["Sachdeva S. The dermatoses of pregnancy. Indian J Dermatol. 2008;53(3):103-105. doi:10.4103/0019-5154.43203"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"19663"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2573"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"19663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/19663"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-04-07T11:34:56+09:30","updatedAt":"2023-04-07T11:34:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2573"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"34718"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji